{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3641f866-3637-4163-a53f-5dee77a962d8","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues found:\n\n### 1. **Recursive wildcard glob** (line 9, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` forces MSBuild to walk the entire directory tree during evaluation. This is the most expensive pattern here — evaluation time grows with every file in the repo. Use a targeted path or specific extensions instead (e.g., `src\\**\\*.cs`).\n\n### 2. **File I/O via property function** (line 13, `EvalHeavy.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` during evaluation performs synchronous disk I/O on every evaluation pass (IDE, restore, build, etc.). Property functions that do I/O should be avoided or deferred to a target that runs only when needed.\n\n### 3. **Deeply chained imports** (`level1.props` → `level2.props` → `level3.props`)\nThree levels of transitive imports each add an XML parse + evaluation pass. While modest here, this pattern scales poorly. Flattening the chain or consolidating into a single `.props` file reduces evaluation overhead.\n\n### Severity ranking\n| Issue | Impact |\n|---|---|\n| Recursive `**\\*.*` glob | **High** — O(files in tree) on every evaluation |\n| `File::ReadAllText` property function | **Medium** — disk I/O on every evaluation |\n| 3-deep import chain | **Low** — constant cost, but compounds in large solutions |\n\nThe glob and the file-read are the actionable items; the import chain is worth noting but less critical.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ccc4dd87-0a81-463f-bbd2-f452afdc0ba8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":480,"requestId":"1C12:190179:1949D82:1CACDE6:69E82117"},"id":"c4c717d5-3440-48ab-8663-c3376d5dec33","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:15:22.019Z","parentId":"a960732c-62d0-4665-b485-9c97f955aede"}
